 III. Human rights violations by all duty bearers ............................................................  6&#8211;<footnote name="6">. The right to life, liberty and security continued to be an issue of serious concern 
during the reporting period as a result of various forms of violence. By 29 November 2012, 
130 civilians, including 40 children and 14 women, had been killed due to conflict-related 
violence in Gaza, such as air strikes, bombardments, incursions and levelling operations, as 
well as the use of live ammunition to enforce the access-restricted areas both on land and at 
sea. Of these, 101 civilians, including 33 children and 13 women, were killed in the crisis 
from 14 to 22 November. Excluding Palestinians injured during the crisis &#8211; as this 
information was not yet verified at the time of writing &#8211; 369 civilians, including 114 
children and 39 women, were injured in Gaza as a result of conflict-related violence during 
the reporting period.5  
