closely monitored the situation and noted, on numerous occasions, the failure of both 
parties to respect the laws of war, including the principles of distinction, proportionality and 
precautions. 
</p>
<p>4. It should be noted that in March 2012 the Government of Israel announced in the 
media that its relations with the Human Rights Council and with OHCHR would be 
suspended following the adoption of Council resolution 19/17, in which the Council 
